     <h5 class="fw-bold">MONITORING SYSTEMS FOR NON-TRACK FEATURES</h5>
     <p>You can indicate your privacy desire to have information about your online browsing habits tracked and collected by activating the Do-Not-Track ("DNT") function or setting found in the majority of web browsers, as well as in some mobile operating systems and applications. There is currently no established common technical standard for identifying and utilizing DNT signals. Because of this, we do not presently react to DNT browser signals or any other technique that conveys your preference to be anonymous when browsing the internet. We will update this privacy notice to include information about any new online tracking standards that we are required to adhere to. </p>
